shield /ʃiːld/

(shielding,shielded,shields) 

1. N-COUNT Something or someone which is a shield against a particular danger or risk provides protection from it. 防护物; 保护人 

例： He used his left hand as a shield against the reflecting sunlight. 他用左手遮挡反射过来的阳光。 

2. V-T If something or someone shields you from a danger or risk, they protect you from it. 保护 

例： He shielded his head from the sun with an old sack. 他用一个旧袋子遮住头来防晒。 

3. V-T If you shield your eyes, you put your hand above your eyes to protect them from direct sunlight. 遮挡 

例： He squinted and shielded his eyes. 他眯着眼并遮住眼睛。 

4. N-COUNT A shield is a large piece of metal or leather which soldiers used to carry to protect their bodies while they were fighting. 盾 

例： He clanged his sword three times on his shield. 他用他的剑当当当地敲了3下盾。 

5. N-COUNT A shield is a sports prize or badge that is shaped like a shield. 盾形奖章; 盾形徽章

